description:
&lt;p&gt;If you are looking for work that suits your lifestyle and needs, becoming a Dorset HealthCare Bank Worker could be right for you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Bank workers work flexibly to fill short term staffing shortages within the teams in our organisation. You may be required to work at any time often with not very much notice.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Completing work for the Trust Bank offers you the flexibility of working now and then or for longer; whatever is right for you. We offer a wide range of roles in a variety of locations throughout Dorset.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You can choose the location and shift patterns that suit you and your family needs and commitments. Depending on your experience we can offer you roles within both physical and mental health settings. With our online and smart phone app you can manage your own bookings.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As well as competitive rates of pay you’ll be eligible for many of the benefits offered to substantive staff. These include:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Access to the NHS pension scheme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;An NHS badge entitling you to many NHS benefits&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Unsocial hours enhancements (where applicable)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Paid annual leave as a percentage of work completed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monthly or weekly pay – your choice!&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A comprehensive induction and ongoing mandatory training&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Salary per hour: £9.20 to £9.89 (&lt;em&gt;Band 2&lt;/em&gt;) £10.09 to £10.81 (&lt;em&gt;Band 3&lt;/em&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Trust Bank Admin Team will fully support you from your offer of a bank agreement to booking your first shift.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;What do we need from you?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;NVQ level 2 or 3 in Health and Social Care or,&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Recent experience within a hospital setting or significant experience within a nursing home/care setting as a carer&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Someone used to working independently in a care setting with a minimum level of support&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A minimum of three shifts per month&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Completion and passing of the Prevention and Management of Violence and Aggression (PMVA) course if you want to work within a mental health environment. (please see link)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Employment in this post requires an Enhanced Disclosure and Barring Service (DBS) check.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interviews will be conducted by Skype.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Trust Bank: Email dhc.bank@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
